help:python;help:scripting

     The application can be extended using python scripts,
              which can be executed using :source.
       This is the preferred way of defining key mapping,
    on startup %/<name_of_executable>-config.py is executed.

    Scripts can communicate with application via gf module.
To see command line functions in gf module type :help python gf1.
   To see other functions of gf module type :help python gf2.

                 Functions can throw exceptions.
                If your script throws exception,
              error message will be shown to user.
